Sounds from a flock of Ring-billed Gulls.  There was one gull in particular that was chasing some of the other birds and calling almost continuously with high, squealing calls, frequently breaking into long calls.  I tried to keep the parabola aimed at this bird as much as possible while recording due to its frequent vocalizations.  Wing noise of flying gulls also heard.  Normalized to -3 dB except for voice announcement at -10 dB. 24-bit/48 kHz WAV file edited with Ocenaudio. Unfiltered.
